The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	Ashok Dinda, who did not play Bengals Ranji match against Gujarat because of fever, will play against Tamil Nadu from December 1, in Chennai. Dinda will be leaving for Chennai on Sunday morning, while the rest of the team will be going directly from Ahmedabad.       
	In another development, at the CAB working committee meeting held Saturday, it was approved that in CAB league matches, draws will be done away with from this season.           
	 Bengal took a vital first-innings lead of 212 runs, with Sreyansh Ghosh and Kaushik Mondal scoring a century each, at the end of the second day, against Assam, in the U-16 Vijay Merchant Trophy match, being played at the JU Salt Lake campus, on Saturday.      
	Brief scores: Assam 218. Bengal 430/7 in 117 overs (S. Ghosh 147, K. Mondal 100, A. Easwaran 57, P. Chakraborty 48 batting; R. Ahmed 3/94). Match to continue.          
	 In the new fixtures released by the Indian Football Association on Saturday, Mohun Bagans last Calcutta Football League Premier Division match, against BNR, has been preponed by a day. The tie will now be played on Monday.                                                                                                                                                       
